Primary_Text: Da bi, ananse kɔtuu bayerɛ akɛseɛ dɛdɛ bi firi n'afuo mu
Translated_Text: One day, Spider went to uproot some big and tasty yams from his farm

Primary_Text: ɔnyaa abotare totoo bayerɛ no ma na etu hwa yie
Translated_Text: He patiently roasted the yam and it smelled very well

Primary_Text: ɛsiane sɛ na ɛyɛ dɛ nti na ɔpɛ sɛ ɔdi no ntɛm
Translated_Text: because they were sweet, he wanted to eat them quickly

Primary_Text: Ankyɛ biara na ɔtee sɛ obi rebɔ ne pono mu
Translated_Text: Not long afterwards, he heard that someone was knocking at his door

Primary_Text: Na ɛyɛ  akyekyedeɛ na ɔrebɔ pono no mu
Translated_Text: It was turtle who was knocking at the door

Primary_Text: Na akyekyedeɛ firi akwantuo mu nti na ɔaberɛ
Translated_Text: Turtle was returning from a journey so he was tired

Primary_Text: Afei nso na ɛkɔm de no yie
Translated_Text: And also he was very hungry

Primary_Text: Akyekyedeɛ ka kyerɛɛ ananse sɛ ɔnam na bayerɛ bi pampan faa ne hwene mu
Translated_Text: Turtle told spider that he was walking around and he smelled the scent/aroma of yam

Primary_Text: na esiane sɛ ɛkɔm de no nti
Translated_Text: and because he is hungry

Primary_Text: ɔyɛɛ n'adwene sɛ ɔbɛba abɛserɛ no
Translated_Text: he made up his mind that he will come and beg him

Primary_Text: sɛ ɔbɛma no bi adi a
Translated_Text: if he will give him some to eat

Primary_Text: Na ɛyɛ amaneɛ wɔ kurom hɔ sɛ sɛ obi srɛ wo aduane a
Translated_Text: It was a custom in the town that if someone begs you for food...

Primary_Text: ɛsɛ sɛ wo ma no bi
Translated_Text: you have to give him/her some

Primary_Text: enti na ananse ntumi nka sɛ daabi
Translated_Text: so ananse could not say no
ananse is greedy

Primary_Text: nti na ɔmpɛ sɛ ɔma akyekyedeɛ bayerɛ no bi di.
Translated_Text: so he did not want to give turtle some of the yam to eat

Primary_Text: ɔbɔɔ pɔ wɔ ne tiri mu sɛ ɔmma no ndi bayerɛ no bi.
Translated_Text: he made a point in his mind that he will not allow turtle to eat some of the yam

Primary_Text: Ananse buee ɛpono no ma akyekyedeɛ wuraa ɛdan no mu
Translated_Text: Ananse opened the door for turtle to enter the room

Primary_Text: Na ɔmaa no akonwa tenaa so
Translated_Text: and he gave him a chair to sit on (it)

Primary_Text: Akyekyedeɛ tenee ne nsa sɛ ɔrebɛyi bayerɛ no bi pɛ
Translated_Text: Just as turtle stretched his hand to remove some of the yam,

Primary_Text: na ananse teaa no kaa sɛ
Translated_Text: and spider shouted at him saying that

Primary_Text: "wonnim sɛ yɛhohoro yɛn nsa ansa na yadidi"
Translated_Text: dont you know that we wash our hands before we eat?
Turtle looked at his palms

Primary_Text: ampa nso na emu ayɛ fi paa yie
Translated_Text: Truly, it was very dirty

Primary_Text: nti ɔsɔre kɔɔ nsuo bi a na ɛda hɔ ho
Translated_Text: so he got up and went to a river that was there
that he was going to wash his hands

Primary_Text: ɔsan baa dan no mu no na ananse ahyɛ aseɛ redi aduane no
Translated_Text: when he came back to the room, ananse had already started eating the food
Ananse told turtle that...

Primary_Text: na ɔmpɛ sɛ aduane no bɛdwo
Translated_Text: he didnt want the food to get cold

Primary_Text: nti na ɔhyɛɛ aseɛ dii aduane no
Translated_Text: that is why he started to eat the food

Primary_Text: nti sɛ ɔaba deɛ a ɔbɛtumi abɛdi bi
Translated_Text: so if he has come he can come and eat some
Turtle sat down again

Primary_Text: nanso ɔsan tenee ne nsa sɛ ɔreyi aduane no bi pɛ
Translated_Text: but again,  when he stretched his hand to take some of the food...

Primary_Text: na ananse san teaa mu bisaa no...
Translated_Text: spider again shouted and asked him ...

Primary_Text: enti woante sɛ yɛmfa nsa fin ndidi
Translated_Text: so didn't you hear that we don't eat with dirty hands

Primary_Text: Akyekyedeɛ hwɛɛ ne nsa mu huu sɛ asan ayɛ fin biom
Translated_Text: turtle looked at his hands and saw that it had become dirty again

Primary_Text: nti ɔsɔre san kɔɔ nsuo no ho sɛ ɔrekɔhohoro ne nsa.
Translated_Text: so he got up again to go to the river side to wash his hands

Primary_Text: esiane sɛ na ɔmpɛ sɛ ne nsa mu bɛyɛ fin biom no nti
Translated_Text: because he didnt want his hands to become dirty again so

Primary_Text: ɔwieeɛ no ɔnantee nsensan no so baa n'akyi
Translated_Text: when he finished, he walked on the grass on his way back

Primary_Text: sɛ deɛ ɛbɛyɛ a ne nsa mu nyɛ fin biom.
Translated_Text: so that his hands will not become dirty again

Primary_Text: Awerɛhosɛm ne sɛ ɔduruu dan no mu no
Translated_Text: sadly, when he got to the room...

Primary_Text: na ananse adi aduane no awie.
Translated_Text: and spider had finished eating the food

Primary_Text: Anokwa ɛhyee akyekyedeɛ yie nanso ɔanka hwee.
Translated_Text: Truly, it pained turtle a lot but he didnt say anything

Primary_Text: ɔhwɛɛ ananse anim kakra na ɔdaa no ase .
Translated_Text: he looked at ananse briefly and thanked him

Primary_Text: ɔka kyerɛɛ ananse sɛ berɛ biara ɔbɛfa ne fie ho no ...
Translated_Text: he told spider that anytime he passes around his house ...

Primary_Text: ɛyɛ a ɔnwura mu na ɔmbɛdidi
Translated_Text: he should come in to eat

Primary_Text: Adufuropɛ nti, akyekyedeɛ asɛm no yɛɛ ananse dɛ
Translated_Text: Because of greed, turtle's issue (the dinner invitation) made spider happy

Primary_Text: Da koro bi, ɔyɛɛ n'adwene sɛ ɔbɛkɔ akyekyedeɛ fie akɔdidi.
Translated_Text: one day, he made up his mind that he will go to turtle's house to eat

Translated_Text: he met turtle sunbathing at the bank of a river

Primary_Text: Akyekyedeɛ pagyaa ne ti na ɔhuu ananse
Translated_Text: Turtle raised his head and saw spider

Primary_Text: ɔmaa no akwaaba bisaa no sɛ aduane no nti na ɔaba anaa
Translated_Text: he welcomed him and asked if he had come because of the food

Primary_Text: ma ananse nso kaa sɛ aane
Translated_Text: cause spider to also say yes

Translated_Text: but because he is not heavy
he couldnt go under it

Primary_Text: ɔyɛɛ biara nanso na ɔntumi nwura nsuo no mu
Translated_Text: He did everything but he wasnt able to enter the water (go under the water)

Primary_Text: ne nyinaa akyi nso na akyekyedeɛ deɛ ɔredi aduane no
Translated_Text: and beside it all turtle was eating the food

Primary_Text: Ananse twaa ne ho twaa ne ho saa

Primary_Text: na afei adwene bi baa ne tiri mu
Translated_Text: and then an idea came to his mind

made him heavy (caused him to become heavy)

Primary_Text: Esiane sɛ ne mu yɛɛ duru no nti

Primary_Text: otumi too ne ho too nsuo no ase.
Translated_Text: he was able to go(throw himself) under the water
he went and sat at the table

Turtle told him that....
as for his town
we dont wear a Jacket when we are eating

Translated_Text: As soon as spider removed the jacket

Oh! it is hitting the housefly

Primary_Text: ᴐabᴐ no ama seisei nwansena no awu
Translated_Text: It has hit it and has caused the housefly to die
The cat has rested
It is relieved

Primary_Text: ᴐde ne nsa reprɛprɛ nwansena no ahwɛ sɛ ᴐawu a
Translated_Text: It is tapping the housefly with its hand to see if it is dead
No, it is not dead!

Primary_Text: ᴐkra no asan abᴐ no ato hᴐ nti ᴐretwan ne ho wᴐ nwansena no ho
Translated_Text: The cat has hit it onto the floor again so it is circling the housefly

Primary_Text: ᴐde amirika afa akonwa no akyi

Primary_Text: Afei ᴐkra no akᴐhyɛ paper no ase rehwɛ sɛ nwansena no awu ampa a
Translated_Text: Now the cat has gone hidden under the paper to see if the housefly is really dead
True, the housefly is dead
The cat has gone and looked at the man

Translated_Text: It is calling the man that he should look that it has killed the housefly

Primary_Text: nanso still aa papa no ɛngye so

Primary_Text: nti ᴐatam nwansena no ahyɛ n' ano mu de akᴐto papa no so

Primary_Text: ᴐahwɛ ara nso still papa no nsᴐre.

Primary_Text: ᴐkra no atam nwansena no ahyɛ papa no ano mu

Primary_Text: Afei deɛ papa no ate n’ani

He has held his neck

Primary_Text: ᴐpɛ sɛ ᴐfe nwansena no nanso ɛmba

Primary_Text: ᴐaka akyerɛ no sɛ biribi hyɛ n' anum
